This directory tree contains the Mythryl compiler back end
upper half, which is concerned with high-level machine-independent
optimization.  To locate this within the larger compiler context
see

    src/lib/compiler/README.

The back end upper half started life as the YALE FLINT project,
which has a home page here:

    http://flint.cs.yale.edu/

For introductory background reading, try Zhon Shao's PhD thesis
with the group:

    Compiling Standard ML for Efficient Execution on Modern Machines
    http://flint.cs.yale.edu/flint/publications/zsh-thesis.html

Nomenclature:  Throughout this code, "fps" is "fate-passing-style".


